{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848503225,"sessionID":"ses_287309294ffetYBdBvl9AcZJkI","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf7a39001eKGuCHAjLWKhzq","messageID":"msg_d78cf6e59001YyT5H86eGPQNUG","sessionID":"ses_287309294ffetYBdBvl9AcZJkI","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_117a265510664ca5a13de029","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - what directories exist, what's the layout\n2. Any existing cmd/ directory or CLI-related code\n3. Any existing tasks.md, plan files, or design documents related to AR-019 or ST-3\n4. The Go module structure (go.mod, imports, existing packages)\n5. Any existing binaries or main.go files\n6. Any design documents, specs, or architecture docs that mention \"AR-019\", \"CLI\", \"binaries\", \"ST-3\", or \"Stage ST-3\"\n7. Look for any pattern of how tasks.md or checklists are formatted in this project\n\nSearch broadly:\n- Look at the root directory structure\n- Search for any files containing \"AR-019\", \"ST-3\", \"CLI\", \"binary\", \"cmd\"\n- Look for any existing tasks.md or similar checklist files\n- Check for go.mod and understand the module name\n- Look at any existing main.go or cmd/ packages\n- Search for design docs, specs, or planning documents\n\nReturn ALL findings in detail - file paths, content snippets, directory listings, and any relevant context about how this project is structured and how tasks are tracked.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2873066b6ffec0afKmJ8iFFpED (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project -- Thorough Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project root is at:\n`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z`\n\n**Root-level directories and files:**\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md          -- SDD (Structured Design Document) prompt used for AR-019\n├── changes/                 -- All change requests (AR-001 through AR-019)\n├── ci-cd/                   -- CI/CD design + spec\n├── cli-toolkit/             -- Python CLI design + spec\n├── client-go/               -- Generated K8s typed client (clientset, informers, listers)\n├── cmd/                     -- Binary entry points (2 exist, 2 planned)\n├── code-execution/          -- Code execution design + spec\n├── coverage.out             -- Go test coverage output\n├── delta-spec.md            -- Root-level delta spec (AR-016)\n├── deployment/              -- Deployment design, spec, client-go reference\n├── design.md                -- Root-level design doc (AR-016: PicoD File Management)\n├── go.mod                   -- Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n├── go.sum                   -- Go dependency checksums\n├── idle-cleanup/            -- Idle cleanup design + spec\n├── integrations/            -- (empty or minimal)\n├── pkg/                     -- All Go library packages\n├── project.md               -- Project context document (OpenSpec format)\n├── proposal.md              -- AR-019 proposal (root-level)\n├── python-sdk/              -- Python SDK design + spec\n├── sandbox-orchestration/   -- Sandbox orchestration design\n├── session-routing/         -- Session routing design + spec\n├── session-store/           -- Session store design + spec\n├── test_spec.md             -- Test specification\n└── testing/                 -- Testing utilities\n```\n\n**Key observation:** There is NO `Makefile` in the project root. The proposal.md references one but it does not exist yet.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing `cmd/` Directory and CLI-Related Code\n\nThe `cmd/` directory currently has **2 subdirectories** (2 existing binaries):\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   └── main.go              -- 59 lines, controller-runtime manager\n└── picod/\n    └── main.go              -- 15 lines, gin HTTP server\n```\n\n**`cmd/agentd/main.go`** (59 lines):\n- Uses `controller-runtime` manager pattern\n- Registers `corev1` and `sandboxv1alpha1` (Sandbox CR) schemes\n- Creates a manager with metrics and health probes disabled\n- Registers `agentd.Reconciler` and starts the manager\n- Uses zap logger\n\n**`cmd/picod/main.go`** (15 lines):\n- Minimal entry point\n- Calls `picod.ParseFlags()` -> `picod.NewServer(config)` -> `server.Run()`\n- Uses `klog` for logging\n\n**Missing binaries (per AR-019 design.md):**\n- `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` -- marked as `[TODO] CLI entry point`\n- `cmd/router/main.go` -- marked as `[TODO] CLI entry point`\n\n---\n\n### 3. AR-019 and ST-3 Related Files\n\n**AR-019 directory:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/`\n\nContains 4 files:\n| File | Lines | Status |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | 69 | Mostly TODO placeholders (English template with Chinese headings) |\n| `design.md` | 841 | **Fully populated** -- comprehensive design with code samples |\n| `delta-spec.md` | 276 | **Fully populated** -- Gherkin-style scenarios |\n| `tasks.md` | 19 | **Empty skeleton** -- only TODO comments |\n\n**Root-level AR-019 files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` -- 259 lines, **fully populated** with a DIFFERENT design than the one in `changes/AR-019/`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` -- 256 lines, the prompt used to generate the design\n\n**Critical discrepancy found:** The root-level `proposal.md` and the `changes/AR-019/` documents describe **different architectures**:\n\n| Aspect | Root `proposal.md` | `changes/AR-019/` docs |\n|--------|-------------------|------------------------|\n| 4 binaries | `agentd`, `picod`, `agentcube` (CLI), `agentcube-controller` | `agentd`, `picod`, `workloadmanager`, `router` |\n| New binaries | `cmd/agentcube/`, `cmd/agentcube-controller/` | `cmd/workloadmanager/`, `cmd/router/` |\n| CLI framework | `spf13/cobra` | Standard `flag` package |\n| Design | User-facing CLI + controller | Wire up existing pkg/ code to main.go |\n\nThe `changes/AR-019/` documents (design.md, delta-spec.md) align with the `workloadmanager` + `router` approach. The root `proposal.md` appears to be an earlier/different iteration.\n\n**ST-3 references:** Every `tasks.md` in the project (AR-002 through AR-019) references \"Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\" as a precondition. ST-3 is the design-completion stage in this project's workflow.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Go Module Structure\n\n**Module name:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go version:** 1.25.0\n\n**Key direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` v1.10.0\n- `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` v5.2.2\n- `github.com/google/uuid` v1.6.0\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` v1.22.0\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` v9.18.0\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.73\n- `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` v2.37.0 (for testing)\n- `k8s.io/api` v0.34.1\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery` v0.34.1\n- `k8s.io/client-go` v0.34.1\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` v0.22.2\n\n**`pkg/` package layout:**\n```\npkg/\n├── agentd/                    -- Reconciler for idle sandbox cleanup\n│   ├── reconciler.go\n│   ├── reconciler_test.go\n│   └── const.go\n├── apis/\n│   ├── agents/v1alpha1/       -- Sandbox CR types\n│   │   ├── sandbox_types.go\n│   │   └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n│   └── runtime/v1alpha1/      -- AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types\n│       ├── agent_type.go\n│       ├── codeinterpreter_types.go\n│       ├── constants.go\n│       ├── groupversion_info.go\n│       ├── shared_types.go\n│       └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n├── common/types/\n│   └── types.go               -- Shared type constants\n├── picod/                     -- In-sandbox daemon (code execution + files)\n│   ├── execute.go, auth.go, types.go\n│   ├── files/                 -- File management subpackage\n│   │   ├── read.go, mkdir.go, types.go, etc.\n│   └── (various test files)\n├── router/                    -- Reverse proxy gateway (16 files)\n│   ├── server.go, config.go, proxy.go, router.go\n│   ├── jwt.go, middleware.go, session_manager.go\n│   ├── informer.go, backend.go, loadbalancer.go\n│   ├── health.go, errors.go\n│   └── (test files)\n├── store/                     -- Redis/Valkey session store (9 files)\n│   ├── store.go               -- Store interface\n│   ├── store_redis.go, store_valkey.go\n│   ├── singleton.go, codec.go\n│   └── (test files)\n└── workloadmanager/           -- Sandbox orchestration API\n    ├── reconciler/            -- SandboxReconciler (informer + workqueue)\n    │   ├── reconciler.go, types.go, sync.go, pod.go\n    │   ├── agentruntime.go, codeinterpreter.go\n    │   ├── event_handlers.go, metrics.go\n    ├── handler/               -- HTTP handlers\n    │   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go, sandbox_create.go, sandbox_delete.go\n    │   ├── models.go, constants.go\n    └── response/\n        └── response.go        -- HTTP response helpers\n```\n\n**`client-go/` (generated):**\n```\nclient-go/\n├── clientset/                 -- Versioned clientset\n├── informers/                 -- Shared informer factory\n└── listers/                   -- Lister implementations\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing Binaries and main.go Files\n\n**Only 2 main.go files exist:**\n\n| File | Lines | Status |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/agentd/main.go` | 59 | Existing, functional |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/picod/main.go` | 15 | Existing, functional |\n\n**No binaries exist in `bin/` directory** (no `bin/` directory at all).\n\n**No `cmd/workloadmanager/` or `cmd/router/` directories exist yet.**\n\n---\n\n### 6. Design Documents Mentioning AR-019, CLI, Binaries, ST-3\n\n**Files containing \"AR-019\":**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/design.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` (root-level)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md`\n\n**Files containing \"ST-3\":**\n- All 16 `tasks.md` files in `changes/AR-*/` reference \"Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\"\n\n---\n\n### 7. Tasks.md / Checklist Format Patterns\n\nThe project uses a consistent pattern for `tasks.md` files. Here are the two main formats observed:\n\n**Format A (Newer ARs: AR-014 through AR-019):**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX — <Title> — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** <pkg path>\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** <S/M/L>\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-XXX/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-XXX/design.md`, `changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. <Task Name>\n\n- [ ] 1.1 <subtask description>\n- [ ] 1.2 <subtask description>\n\n**Verification:** <how to verify>\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n<ASCII dependency graph>\n\n**Parallel execution:**\n<description>\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | <criterion> | `<command>` |\n```\n\n**Format B (Older ARs: AR-002 through AR-013):**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX 任务清单\n\n> **Stage**: ST-3 (Design Complete)\n> **AR**: AR-XXX — <title>\n> **Module**: `<pkg path>`\n> **Language**: Go\n> **Size**: <S/M/L>\n\n---\n\n## T-001: <Task Name>\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 <subtask>\n- [ ] T-001.02 <subtask>\n\n**验收**: <verification>\n\n---\n\n## 依赖关系\n\n<ASCII dependency graph>\n\n## 文件产出清单\n\n| 文件 | 状态 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|\n```\n\n**Key conventions across all tasks.md files:**\n- Tasks are numbered (T1, T2... or T-001, T-002...)\n- Subtasks use decimal notation (1.1, 1.2 or T-001.01, T-001.02)\n- Each task ends with a **Verification** / **验收** line\n- Task dependency graph is ASCII art\n- Acceptance Criteria table maps criterion ID to verification command\n- Tasks reference specific design.md sections and delta-spec scenarios\n- Tasks always end with a \"code quality gate\" task (build, test, vet, race, mod tidy)\n\n**AR-019 tasks.md is currently an empty skeleton** with only 19 lines and 3 TODO comments -- it needs to be filled in following the patterns above.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **AR-019 is at the implementation stage** -- design.md and delta-spec.md are fully written, but tasks.md is an empty skeleton and no code has been created yet.\n\n2. **Two new binaries need to be created:** `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` and `cmd/router/main.go` (per the `changes/AR-019/` design docs). The design.md even contains full code samples for both.\n\n3. **The existing pkg/ code is already complete** -- `pkg/workloadmanager/`, `pkg/router/`, `pkg/store/` all have substantial implementations. The AR-019 task is essentially wiring these existing packages into `main.go` entry points.\n\n4. **There is a design discrepancy** between the root-level `proposal.md` (which proposes `agentcube` CLI + `agentcube-controller`) and the `changes/AR-019/` documents (which propose `workloadmanager` + `router`). The `changes/AR-019/` documents appear to be the more recent and detailed version.\n\n5. **No Makefile exists** despite being referenced in the proposal.md.\n\n6. **The tasks.md format is well-established** with clear patterns for task numbering, subtasks, verification commands, dependency graphs, and acceptance criteria tables.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2873066b6ffec0afKmJ8iFFpED","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775848364357,"end":1775848503222}}}}
